content:
@WG-prioritization/alerts issue #83737 has been requested for prioritization.

Procedure

  • Priority?
  • Regression?
  • Notify people/groups?
  • Needs I-nominated?

I've checked other open+closed issues with ~same error but I'm not sure this is a duplicate.
If it makes sense, I'd wait for a minimal repro before deciding on a priority. At a first glance it looks like a regression that broke working code (so P-high)

the culprit PR was merged 15 hours ago so I don't think there's a duplicate issue yet.
Agree with waiting for a MCVE and P-high (or even P-critical, if it likely causes ICE on other crates)
Issue author is testing a patch to see if it fixes the problem. Hopefully it'll work!
I think I'll assign a P-high, being this issue already under control
